---+++++ Updated Statistics using the Register:

I am now using a different definition for categories that resembles the actual structure of the Fachsystematik more closely. Instead of main and subcategories, I now use category "levels", of which there are four. the lowest (0) is the most specific and higher levels are progressively more general with level 3 being just five very general categories.

This data is *far* more accurate than the previous batch, Instead of 190 words for classification I can now use 3850 and the share of documents that cannot be classified has decreased from ~20% to ~0.5%.

The following statistics show the number of categories per document for the amount of documents (with that number of categories), on all 4 levels.

A statistic concerning the frequency of a certain category within documents can be found [[ClemensDeusserCategoryFrequency][here]].

